{
  "text": "In 1965, Campbell [CITATION_1] gave an operational meaning to R\u00e9nyi entropy. He showed that, instead of the expected code lengths, if one minimizes the cumulants of code lengths, then the optimal cumulant is the R\u00e9nyi entropy. He also showed that the optimal cumulant can be achieved by encoding sufficiently long sequences of symbols. In 1988, Blumer and",
